Steps to build on linux:
1. Run the provided shell script runscript.sh

Steps to build on windows:
1. Launch cmake-gui
2. Set the source path to
D:/_help_/cpp/cmake_tutorial
3. Set the build path to
D:/_help_/cpp/cmake_tutorial/build
4. Configure (select the current generator: MinGW Makefiles)
5. Edit any CMAKE Variables if the Configure fails and then Configure again
7. Generate to generate the makefile
8. Open a terminal and navigate to the build folder and make (make sure
that the terminal has environment variable set for the MinGW compiler)
9. Launch the executable "tutorial" generated in the src folder
10. If there is missing dll error, copy the required dll in src and launch again